The paper discusses the design and validation of a test structure for interconnect parasitic in on-chip machine learning accelerators. This involves aspects of electronic design automation (EDA), circuit design, and hardware implementation, which are covered by the cs.ET (Electronic Design Automation) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of empirical models to estimate RC parasitic, which falls under the cs.EM (Electromagnetics) sub-category. The focus on interconnects and their impact on system performance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.VLSI (Very Large Scale Integration) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning accelerators suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
